The paper deals with automatic video annotation using visual similarity and collective knowledge embedded in user-generated tags and web sources. This involves techniques related to computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of web sources like Google and Bing, which falls under the category of web search (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
